NRTs will not have to worry about the bureaucratic irritants like running around departments as the corporation will take care of them. The expectations of the West to have a corporation work on a par with western standards is realised today, Ravikumar P. Vemuru, advisor to the State government on NRT affairs and investments, told The Hindu .He announced that escort officers would be provided to the NRTs till their units start production.Dr. Vemuru predicted a huge success for the initiative going by the adoption of 362 villages in a month and a half and the interest evinced by 76 companies to set up base in the State. He has set an ambitious target of getting 1,000 villages adopted soon, besides generation of over Rs.10,000-crore investment every year.